<item>
            <title>[NET-264] Telnet spyStream NullPointerException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-264</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Calling stopSpyStream on TelnetClient sets spyStream to null without regard to whether _spyRead or _spyWrite are being invoked on another thread. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Resulting NPE in _spyRead/_spy_Write is caught in TelnetInputStream.run() which goes on to close the stream.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;May be able to fix by taking local copy of spyStream (which ought also to be volatile) in both of _spyRead and _spyWrite. E.g. for _spyRead:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    void _spyRead(int ch)&lt;br/&gt;
    {&lt;br/&gt;
        OutputStream _spyStream = spyStream;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        if (_spyStream != null)&lt;br/&gt;
        {&lt;br/&gt;
            try&lt;br/&gt;
            {&lt;br/&gt;
                if (ch != &apos;\r&apos;)&lt;br/&gt;
                {&lt;br/&gt;
                    _spyStream.write(ch);&lt;br/&gt;
                    if (ch == &apos;\n&apos;)&lt;/p&gt;
                    {
                        _spyStream.write(&apos;\r&apos;);
                    }
&lt;p&gt;                    _spyStream.flush();&lt;br/&gt;
                }&lt;br/&gt;
            }&lt;br/&gt;
            catch (IOException e)&lt;/p&gt;
            {
                spyStream = null;
            }
&lt;p&gt;        }&lt;br/&gt;
    }&lt;/p&gt;</description>
